The game was a rollercoaster of emotions, with the Nittany Lions overcoming a 10-point deficit to secure the win. The clash marked the first meeting between the two programs in more than a decade and was highly anticipated as a battle between two blue bloods. Despite USC's loss, Coach Lincoln Riley acknowledged his team's shortcomings and expressed resolve to address them. The game garnered significant media attention, with experts analyzing various aspects, including key moments, TV and streaming options, and game predictions. Additionally, the upcoming Maryland-USC matchup on October 19th has been announced, providing fans with another opportunity to witness a captivating game.

name: Baba Siddique
summary: Former Maharashtra Minister and NCP leader Baba Siddique was tragically shot dead outside his son's MLA office in Mumbai. The Mumbai Police has identified two alleged accused in connection with the murder and revealed the involvement of gangster Lawrence Bishnoi's gang, based on the claims of the assailants. In response, the Maharashtra Chief Minister has ordered a state funeral for Siddique. Salman Khan has postponed the shoot of Bigg Boss 18 to pay his respects to Siddique's family, while the investigation into the motive and circumstances surrounding the murder continues.

name: Ariana Grande
summary: In her appearance on "Saturday Night Live," Ariana Grande showcased her vocal prowess by imitating legendary singers like Britney Spears, Celine Dion, and Miley Cyrus. She shared her long-held dream of starring in "Wicked," which she had pursued for over a decade. In her hilarious promo, Grande revealed her reluctance to perform "Wicked" skits, much to the dismay of the cast. Grande's Celine Dion impression took a comical twist as she romanticized UFC fighting in a parody theme song. She also addressed body-shaming in a "Brat" remix with Charli XCX, calling out scrutiny over her weight. The "Sympathy is a Knife" remix with Charli XCX explored themes of self-compassion. Mariah Carey expressed her admiration after Grande labeled her the "queen of my life." Grande and Bowen Yang's collaboration lured Stevie Nicks into singing in an "SNL" promo, and a cut-for-time sketch featured Grande belting out "Get Happy" as Judy Garland.
